# Agent docs: read before, update after

Before making changes or answering questions about how SMD behaves, read
`agent-docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` (module map, data flow, gotchas) and
`agent-docs/DECISIONS.md` (why non-obvious choices were made). They exist so
you don't have to re-derive the whole codebase from scratch every session.

These are navigation aids, not a spec - they can go stale. If a user
question is about exact current behavior (especially anything touching data
safety, file deletion, or matching/verification logic), verify against the
actual source file/function before answering, don't just trust the doc.

After any structural or behavioral change (new module, changed data flow,
changed default, changed concurrency/safety behavior), update the relevant
section of `ARCHITECTURE.md`. If the change involved a non-obvious "why"
(a trade-off, a bug root-cause, a rejected alternative), add a dated entry
to the top of `DECISIONS.md` instead of leaving the reasoning only in chat.

Keep both files terse and pointing at real file/function names rather than
duplicating code. Don't create empty placeholder sections "to fill in
later" - only add content once it's verified against the actual code.
